basic.floral_language:
Digitalis x fulva
Floriography: beautiful, vivid, lovely
Digitalis x fulva is an herb plant with graceful shape and dark green oval leaves, huge flowers in bell-shape, slightly drooping and open from bottom to top along the stem, like sounding horns, vivid and lovely. Suitable for flower beds or garden landscaping.
Digitalis x fulva likes adequate sunlight, slightly resistant to half shade, shade properly in summer to avoid strong sunlight. Flower in May-June for 2-3 weeks viewing.
basic.blooming: Flowering period May-June, viewing period 2-3 weeks

maintenance.soil: Peat or soil with specific nutrients
maintenance.sunlight: Like adequate light, resistant to half shade, avoid strong direct light in summer
maintenance.watering: Water thoroughly after soil surface dries
maintenance.fertilization: Dilute fertilizers following instructions, apply once monthly in spring
maintenance.pruning: Remove withered flowers, peduncle, diseased and dead leaves timely
